WEBVTT

00:00.417 --> 00:02.917
<i>In the time of the romance
man battle in arenas</i>

00:02.921 --> 00:04.821
<i>to prove their strengh and valor.</i>

00:04.823 --> 00:06.923
<i>Winning, met life, defeat,</i>

00:07.451 --> 00:08.818
<i>death.</i>

00:08.853 --> 00:10.353
<i>Now they battle in gymnasiums</i>

00:10.388 --> 00:12.589
<i>for letters on their jackets</i>
<i>and cheerleaders on their laps.</i>

00:13.153 --> 00:16.738
Body! Body! Body! Body!

00:21.728 --> 00:24.396
The body cannot be beaten!

00:25.782 --> 00:27.266
The body cannot be beat!

00:31.621 --> 00:33.922
We could cure cancer
or win the Nobel Prize,

00:33.940 --> 00:36.558
and no one would
celebrate us like that.

00:36.576 --> 00:41.163
Body! Body! Body! Body! Body!

00:41.197 --> 00:42.764
I love you, body!

00:42.799 --> 00:46.051
Body! Body! Body!

00:46.052 --> 00:48.954
Body! Body! Body! Body!

00:48.988 --> 00:50.873
They never carried Salinger
down the hallway!

00:51.875 --> 00:54.843
Body! Body! Body!

01:00.855 --> 01:02.389
No.

01:02.423 --> 01:05.358
I can't have a roll?
A roll?

01:05.393 --> 01:06.660
You'll spoil
Ryan's victory dinner.

01:06.694 --> 01:08.962
Ryan has a victory dinner,
like, every other night.

01:08.997 --> 01:10.164
That's because
he's a winner.

01:10.198 --> 01:11.465
Winners are different.

01:11.499 --> 01:13.667
They're not like you...
<i>and</i> me.

01:13.701 --> 01:16.436
So what are we having?

01:16.471 --> 01:19.006
Ryan's favorite...
Venison marinara.

01:19.040 --> 01:22.109
I swear, that boy
will eat <i>anything</i> marinara.

01:22.143 --> 01:23.810
He really will.

01:23.845 --> 01:25.078
Body!

01:25.113 --> 01:28.599
Body! Body! Body! Body!

01:28.650 --> 01:29.733
Did you guys wait
for me to eat?

01:29.784 --> 01:31.451
- Yeah.
- Sorry.

01:31.486 --> 01:32.519
The guys carried me out
for burgers,

01:32.554 --> 01:34.888
- so I had burgers.
- Yeah.

01:34.923 --> 01:35.989
Body!

01:36.023 --> 01:37.758
Body! Body! Body!

01:39.467 --> 01:41.235
That's the nice
thing about deer meat.

01:41.269 --> 01:43.137
- <i>Body! Body</i>!
- It reheats beautifully.

01:43.573 --> 01:44.506
I wouldn't call
this helping.

01:44.540 --> 01:45.507
You said
you were gonna help.

01:45.541 --> 01:46.892
I wanted to help,
but that looks heavy

01:46.926 --> 01:48.944
and smells gross,
and I'm a girl.

01:48.978 --> 01:50.579
Really? You're gonna play
the girl card?

01:50.613 --> 01:52.013
Shame on you, Tessa.

01:52.048 --> 01:53.749
I feel no shame.
Carry your own dirt.

01:53.783 --> 01:55.417
Hey, careful!
Careful...

01:55.451 --> 01:56.418
Of my flower.

01:56.452 --> 01:59.438
You almost trampled
my flower.

01:59.472 --> 02:01.073
- Your flower?
- Yeah.

02:01.107 --> 02:03.125
It's the first thing
to blossom in my garden,

02:03.159 --> 02:04.176
and I'm nurturing it.

02:04.227 --> 02:06.661
You tender, tender soul.

02:06.696 --> 02:09.330
Body! Body! Body!

02:09.365 --> 02:10.999
Body! Body!

02:11.032 --> 02:12.401
B-body.
 Body. Body.

02:12.435 --> 02:13.435
Body.

02:13.469 --> 02:14.403
Body.
Body.

02:14.437 --> 02:15.654
Body.
Body.

02:15.705 --> 02:16.655
Body!
Body.

02:17.774 --> 02:19.591
Dominate at school, champ.

02:19.625 --> 02:21.176
I will, mom.

02:22.762 --> 02:25.914
You have an amazing body.

02:25.948 --> 02:27.432
Thanks, dad.

02:31.120 --> 02:32.421
Bye-bye.

02:32.455 --> 02:34.856
You know, you could be a little
livelier with my send-offs.

02:36.175 --> 02:38.960
Lazy! Lazy! Lazy!

02:38.978 --> 02:41.930
Lazy! Lazy! Lazy!

02:41.964 --> 02:44.282
- Lazy! Lazy! Lazy!
- That's what I'm talking about.

02:44.333 --> 02:46.601
Sync and corrected by dr.jackson
for www.addic7ed.com

02:54.311 --> 02:57.779
I don't know.
They're already pretty white.

02:57.814 --> 03:00.882
Not white enough. I need
to freshen up my curb appeal.

03:00.917 --> 03:03.385
I'm back on the market.

03:03.419 --> 03:04.386
Okay.

03:04.420 --> 03:05.587
So...

03:05.605 --> 03:09.391
What, you're thinking, um...

03:09.425 --> 03:10.892
Picket fence white?

03:10.927 --> 03:13.094
Crazy for cotton balls?

03:13.129 --> 03:15.564
How about that one?

03:15.598 --> 03:17.232
Supremacy white.

03:17.266 --> 03:18.733
Yeah,
I wouldn't recommend that.

03:18.767 --> 03:22.003
Very few people who can
pull off supremacy white.

03:22.038 --> 03:24.556
Let's just say I want to be
the whitest white

03:24.590 --> 03:27.342
you can legally make me.

03:27.376 --> 03:30.412
I can't help but feel like
you're rushing into this.

03:30.446 --> 03:32.080
You're making
a lot of crazy decisions...

03:32.114 --> 03:34.449
And you're not
thinking about the consequences.

03:34.484 --> 03:35.800
Really?

03:35.835 --> 03:38.420
And what kind of crazy decisions
might you be referring to?

03:38.454 --> 03:40.288
My decision
to divorce Steven?

03:40.323 --> 03:41.289
Absolutely not.

03:41.307 --> 03:42.757
Okay.

03:42.791 --> 03:44.509
That's none of my business.

03:44.560 --> 03:46.595
I'm just saying that

03:46.629 --> 03:49.164
your gums have been
through a lot,

03:49.198 --> 03:52.100
and they're sensitive.
They're exposed.

03:52.438 --> 03:53.906
They're single
for the first time in years,

03:53.940 --> 03:55.908
and they're acting
a little desperate.

03:55.942 --> 03:58.277
Thank you for fitting me
in today, Dr. Werner,

03:58.311 --> 03:59.862
but I am gonna take

03:59.896 --> 04:02.981
my single, <i>desperate</i> gums
elsewhere.

04:08.855 --> 04:10.755
Kill it.

04:10.773 --> 04:12.191
Whoa. Hello, Sheila.

04:12.225 --> 04:13.892
Didn't hear you coming.

04:13.927 --> 04:16.060
It's my new gardening clogs.
They're super stealthy,

04:16.970 --> 04:18.370
but they do smell bad
after the rain.

04:18.404 --> 04:19.605
Good to know.

04:19.640 --> 04:21.641
Dig it out by its roots.
It's weak.

04:21.675 --> 04:23.042
It sets a bad precedent
for the others.

04:24.144 --> 04:27.063
Hey, why don't we each
tend to our own gardens, okay?

04:27.097 --> 04:29.966
Have you seen my roses
across the street, George?

04:30.000 --> 04:33.369
They're winners,
each one perfect, and why?

04:33.404 --> 04:35.555
Because I deadhead
the losers.

04:35.589 --> 04:37.757
I don't do it because it's fun,
although it is.

04:37.791 --> 04:40.927
I do it so I can make
the whole garden shine.

04:40.961 --> 04:42.528
Well, I have
a different approach.

04:42.563 --> 04:44.530
I tend to think
anything can flower

04:44.598 --> 04:45.898
with a little encouragement.

04:45.933 --> 04:48.801
Sometimes I wonder
about you, George.

04:48.835 --> 04:50.737
I really do wonder.

04:52.406 --> 04:54.173
Likewise.

04:55.807 --> 04:57.358
<i>Having grown up in the city...</i>

04:57.392 --> 04:58.876
<i>I was at a distinct
disadvantage.</i>

04:58.911 --> 05:00.644
<i>We didn't play outside.</i>

05:00.662 --> 05:02.446
<i>The park was somewhere you went</i>
<i>to buy weed,</i>

05:02.481 --> 05:05.449
<i>and the tall buildings blocked</i>
<i>out all the sunlight.</i>

05:05.467 --> 05:06.750
<i>In sixth grade,</i>

05:06.802 --> 05:08.252
<i>two of the girls in my class</i>
<i>had rickets.</i>

05:08.270 --> 05:09.737
<i>Tessa Altman, please report</i>

05:09.788 --> 05:11.355
<i>to Mr. Wolfe's office.</i>

05:11.390 --> 05:13.007
Me?

05:13.041 --> 05:14.458
Okay.

05:14.493 --> 05:15.826
Tessa, you're failing.

05:15.861 --> 05:18.296
What? That's not possible.
I'm smart.

05:18.330 --> 05:19.497
What class?

05:19.531 --> 05:20.498
Gym class.

05:20.532 --> 05:22.500
That's not a class.

05:22.534 --> 05:24.335
Of course it is a class.

05:24.369 --> 05:26.671
If it weren't a class,
you wouldn't be failing,

05:26.705 --> 05:28.973
which I assure you,
you are.

05:29.007 --> 05:31.776
So what I'm hearing is,
this isn't about A.P. English.

05:31.810 --> 05:35.479
Tessa, this "F" will bring
down your G.P.A.,

05:35.514 --> 05:37.949
so you might want to get real
about your future.

05:37.983 --> 05:41.185
Shall we chat trade schools?

